* React SDK — Full hooks reference
* _——React SDK
* The @alien_org/react package provides React hooks for building mini apps. It wraps the low-level bridge API with React-friendly state management.
* Installation
* npm install @alien_org/react
* Setup
* Wrap your app with AlienProvider:
* import { AlienProvider } from '@alien_org/react';
*  
* function App() {
*   return (
*     <AlienProvider>
*       <YourApp />
*     </AlienProvider>
*   );
* }
* The provider initializes the bridge connection, reads launch parameters, sets safe area CSS variables, and sends app:ready to the host app. See App Lifecycle for details on why app:ready matters.
* AlienProvider Props
Prop	Type	Default	Description
autoReady	boolean	true	Automatically send app:ready on mount. Set to false to defer the ready signal.
interceptLinks	boolean	true	Intercept external link clicks and route them through the bridge.
Hooks Reference
* useAlien
* Access the core context values.
* import { useAlien } from '@alien_org/react';
*  
* const { authToken, contractVersion, isBridgeAvailable, ready } = useAlien();
Property	Type	Description	
authToken	string | undefined	JWT from host app	
contractVersion	Version | undefined	SDK protocol version	
isBridgeAvailable	boolean	true if running in Alien app	
ready	() => void	Signal the host that the miniapp is ready (only needed with autoReady={false})	
useLaunchParams
* Get all launch parameters.
* import { useLaunchParams } from '@alien_org/react';
*  
* const params = useLaunchParams();
* Returns undefined if launch params are unavailable (e.g., running in a browser).
Property	Type	Description	
authToken	string | undefined	JWT from host app	
contractVersion	Version | undefined	SDK protocol version	
hostAppVersion	string | undefined	Host app version	
platform	'ios' | 'android' | undefined	Platform	
startParam	string | undefined	Custom deeplink parameter	
safeAreaInsets	SafeAreaInsets | undefined	Safe area insets ({ top, right, bottom, left })	
useEvent
* Subscribe to events from the host app. Cleanup is automatic on unmount.
* import { useEvent } from '@alien_org/react';
*  
* // Handle back button
* useEvent('host.back.button:clicked', () => {
*   navigateBack();
* });
* useMethod
* Generic hook for request-response bridge methods. Handles loading, error states, and version checking automatically.
* import { useMethod } from '@alien_org/react';
*  
* const { execute, data, error, isLoading, reset, supported } = useMethod(
*   'payment:request',
*   'payment:response',
* );
*  
* const result = await execute({
*   recipient: 'wallet-address',
*   amount: '1000000',
*   token: 'USDC',
*   network: 'solana',
*   invoice: 'order-123',
* });
Property	Type	Description	
execute	(params, options?) => Promise<{ data, error }>	Send the method	
data	EventPayload | undefined	Response data	
error	Error | undefined	Error if failed	
isLoading	boolean	Request in progress	
reset	() => void	Reset state	
supported	boolean	Method supported by host	
usePayment
* Specialized hook for payments with full state management. See Payments for full documentation.
* import { usePayment } from '@alien_org/react';
*  
* const { pay, isPaid, isLoading, txHash, errorCode } = usePayment({
*   onPaid: (txHash) => console.log('Paid!', txHash),
*   onCancelled: () => console.log('Cancelled'),
*   onFailed: (code) => console.log('Failed:', code),
* });
*  
* await pay({
*   recipient: 'wallet-address',
*   amount: '10000',
*   token: 'USDC',
*   network: 'solana',
*   invoice: 'order-123',
* });
* useClipboard
* Read and write to the system clipboard via the host app. See Clipboard for full documentation.
* import { useClipboard } from '@alien_org/react';
*  
* const { writeText, readText, isReading, errorCode, supported } = useClipboard();
* useIsMethodSupported
* Check if a method is supported by the host app version.
* import { useIsMethodSupported } from '@alien_org/react';
*  
* const { supported, minVersion, contractVersion } = useIsMethodSupported('payment:request');
*  
* if (!supported) {
*   return <div>Update the Alien app to use payments (requires {minVersion})</div>;
* }
* useLinkInterceptor
* Intercept external link clicks and route them through the host app. AlienProvider enables this by default. See Link Management for full documentation.
* import { useLinkInterceptor } from '@alien_org/react';
*  
* useLinkInterceptor({ openMode: 'external' });
